<item>
            <title>[HBASE-17038] Allow verifyrep to persist row keys</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-17038</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have been involved in a case where user of verifyrep observed fluctuating row key count during successive runs with time range.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If verifyrep can persist the row keys during current run (to e.g. hdfs) (controlled by a flag), successive run(s) would be able to use this information to find the difference in row keys w.r.t. previous run and perform some actions (such as performing raw scan, etc).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This would allow the user to correlate results from successive runs better.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
